# Integration Standards

## Context
- Apply when the kiosk communicates with external systems: the backend API (ticket catalog sync, receipt webhooks) and the SumUp card reader (platform channel).
- The kiosk must work **offline** — backend unavailability must degrade gracefully, never crash.

## Requirements

### Backend API
- Resource-based URLs, kebab-case, versioned: `/v1/ticket-types`, `/v1/orders`.
- Standard HTTP methods: GET (read), POST (create), PATCH (partial update).
- Use `Dio` for HTTP. Set connect and receive timeouts — never block indefinitely.
- Backend errors return structured JSON; parse into typed `AppError` subclasses — never expose raw HTTP bodies to the UI.
- Include `X-Kiosk-Id` header on all requests (device identifier, not user PII).
- All backend communication over HTTPS. Certificate validation must not be disabled.

### SumUp Platform Channel
- Channel name: `ee.kaasan.museum_kiosk/sumup`.
- The only method exposed: `charge` — takes `orderId`, `amountCents`, `currency`, `title`.
- Returns `{success: bool, transactionCode: String?, errorDetail: String?}`.
- `PlatformException` codes: `TIMEOUT`, `UNAVAILABLE`, `DECLINED` — all mapped to typed `AppError` subclasses in `SumUpPaymentService`.
- No other methods on this channel. Adding new channel methods requires explicit architectural review.

### Offline Resilience
- Ticket catalog is cached in `TicketTypes` table on last successful sync.
- If sync fails, kiosk falls back to cached catalog — display `(cached)` indicator if sync age > 24h.
- Orders are written to local `Orders` table immediately — they survive app restarts.
- Receipts/webhooks to backend are best-effort with retry; failure must not block the confirmation screen.

### Correlation
- Every order has a UUID (`orderId`) generated at cart checkout.
- All logs, DB records, and backend requests for an order reference the same `orderId`.
- SumUp transaction code is stored alongside the order on success.

## Critical Rules
- NEVER make a blocking network call on the main isolate.
- NEVER expose raw HTTP error bodies or stack traces to the kiosk UI — show friendly error messages only.
- ALWAYS set timeouts on all outbound HTTP calls.
- ALWAYS write order to local DB before initiating SumUp charge.
- ALWAYS handle `PlatformException` from the SumUp channel as a typed `AppError`.
- NEVER add new methods to the SumUp platform channel without review.
